{"timestamp": "2025-12-06 13:55:39.031342", "event": "llm_start", "messages": "content='Based on the diagnosis report: Troubleshooting Diagnosis Report\\n\\nSummary of current network health\\n- Overall: The enterprise network is partially degraded. The 10.2.1.0/24 access segment is healthy and fully reaches server farm services. The 10.1.1.0/24 access segment is impaired: the host there has no IP address and cannot reach anything; that subnet is also not present in the OSPF domain.\\n- Core and server-farm side: OSPF adjacencies across core routers and to server_access_router are up. Server farm services (DNS, web servers, load balancer) are reachable from 10.2.1.0/24.\\n\\nKey observations and tests\\n- Reachability matrix:\\n  - host_2_1_1_1 (10.2.1.10) can ping dns_server (10.200.0.2), load_balancer (10.200.0.7), and web servers 0–3 (10.200.0.3–.6) with 0% loss and low RTTs.\\n  - host_1_1_1_1 is unable to ping any server IP; “Network is unreachable” for all attempts.\\n- Host configurations:\\n  - host_1_1_1_1: eth0 up but no IPv4 address, no routes (ip_route empty). Pinging its default gateway 10.1.1.1 fails locally (Network is unreachable).\\n  - host_2_1_1_1: has DHCP-assigned 10.2.1.10/24 with default route via 10.2.1.1 and normal connectivity.\\n- DHCP state:\\n  - dhcp_server lease file shows multiple active leases for 10.2.1.10 (host_2_1_1_1), and a lease for 10.1.1.10 (host_1_1_1_1) that is now free (expired). Current host_1_1_1_1 has no IP.\\n  - router_dist_2_1 is successfully facilitating DHCP for 10.2.1.0/24 (host_2_1_1_1 has a dynamic lease; dhcp_server sees those leases).\\n- Distribution routers and services:\\n  - router_dist_1_1 (10.1.1.1 br0; 172.16.0.7/31 uplink):\\n    - FRR service: inactive (dead). frr commands fail with “failed to connect to any daemons.”\\n    - ISC DHCP relay: inactive (dead).\\n    - Kernel routes: only connected (10.1.1.0/24, 172.16.0.6/31). No OSPF-learned routes.\\n  - router_dist_2_1 (10.2.1.1 br0; 172.16.0.9/31 uplink):\\n    - FRR service active; OSPF routes present (including to 10.200.0.0/24).\\n    - netstat shows UDP 0.0.0.0:67 listening (indicative of DHCP relay/server functionality); host DHCP working.\\n- OSPF domain view:\\n  - Core routers have OSPF neighbors with each other and with router_dist_2_1 and server_access_router; no adjacency with router_dist_1_1 (expected, since FRR there is down).\\n  - server_access_router routes: learns 10.2.1.0/24 via OSPF; does not have 10.1.1.0/24. Pinging 10.1.1.10 from dns_server yields “Destination Net Unreachable” from 10.200.0.1 (server_access_router).\\n- Access switches:\\n  - switch_access_1_1_1 and switch_access_2_1_1 show healthy bridging interfaces; no apparent L2 errors.\\n\\nDetected anomalies\\n1) Host in 10.1.1.0/24 has no IP configuration and no routing:\\n   - host_1_1_1_1 has no IPv4 address nor routes. Local pings fail with “Network is unreachable.”\\n   - dhcp_server shows a past lease for 10.1.1.10 that is now free; no current lease activity for that host.\\n\\n2) Routing for 10.1.1.0/24 is absent from the OSPF domain:\\n   - server_access_router lacks an OSPF route to 10.1.1.0/24 and responds with Net Unreachable toward that network.\\n   - Core routers do not show an OSPF adjacency with router_dist_1_1.\\n\\nFault localization\\n- Primary faulty device: router_dist_1_1 (distribution router for 10.1.1.0/24).\\n  - FRR (OSPF) service is down—inactive (dead).\\n  - ISC DHCP relay service is inactive (dead).\\n  - Consequences:\\n    - No DHCP relay for subnet 10.1.1.0/24; hosts cannot obtain/maintain leases.\\n    - No OSPF adjacency to the core; 10.1.1.0/24 is not advertised, isolating the subnet from the rest of the network.\\n\\n- Affected endpoint: host_1_1_1_1 is a victim of the above, lacking an IP and therefore any reachability.\\n\\nItems assessed as normal/healthy\\n- router_dist_2_1: FRR running, OSPF routes present, DHCP for 10.2.1.0/24 functioning; host_2_1_1_1 reaches all server IPs.\\n- Core OSPF fabric and server_access_router: OSPF adjacencies stable and routes installed for server farm and 10.2.1.0/24.\\n- Server farm devices (dns_server, web_server_0–3, load_balancer): IP connectivity within expected bounds from 10.2.1.0/24.\\n- Access switching: L2 links up with no errors reported.\\n\\nRoot cause analysis\\n- The outage on router_dist_1_1 (two services down) is the root cause of the 10.1.1.0/24 segment issues:\\n  - DHCP relay down prevents host IP assignment/renewal on 10.1.1.0/24.\\n  - FRR/OSPF down prevents 10.1.1.0/24 from being advertised/routes learned by the rest of the network.\\n  - Evidence includes:\\n    - router_dist_1_1: frr inactive; ospf commands fail; only connected routes present.\\n    - server_access_router: no OSPF route to 10.1.1.0/24; Net Unreachable to 10.1.1.10.\\n    - host_1_1_1_1: no IP and no route; ping attempts fail locally.\\n    - dhcp_server: 10.1.1.10 lease shown as free; no current active lease for host_1_1_1_1.\\n\\nConclusion\\n- Network is partially degraded due to service failures on router_dist_1_1. The 10.2.1.0/24 path and server farm side are healthy. The 10.1.1.0/24 segment is effectively isolated and non-functional for hosts because DHCP relay and OSPF are not operating on its distribution router., please provide the submission. Do not submit if no report available.' additional_kwargs={} response_metadata={} id='8571219b-16c4-4c35-923c-9c5eb199e285'", "model": {"lc": 1, "type": "constructor", "id": ["langchain", "chat_models", "openai", "ChatOpenAI"], "kwargs": {"model_name": "gpt-5", "openai_api_key": {"lc": 1, "type": "secret", "id": ["OPENAI_API_KEY"]}, "stream_usage": true}, "name": "ChatOpenAI"}}
